# Docs Agent Rules — wood-showroom-docs

Read all documentation files.

Validation tasks:

- Check that every feature in SPEC.md has at least one task in TASKS.md.
- Check that every API endpoint in API_SPEC.md exists in openapi.yaml.
- Check that every Phase 1 table in DATA_MODEL.md has a corresponding task for schema creation.
- Check that deferred Phase 2 tables/features are clearly marked and not assigned Phase 1 tasks.
- Check that TASKS.md has no duplicate task IDs.
- Check that section numbers in each file are sequential with no duplicates.
- Check that security scheme names are exactly `cookieAuth` and `csrfHeader`.
- Validate openapi.yaml.

Suggested command:

```bash
npx @redocly/cli lint openapi.yaml
```

Report format:

- Issue ID
- Severity
- File
- Section/line if available
- Description
- Suggested fix


Language checks:

- Confirm `LANGUAGE_POLICY.md` exists.
- Confirm FE tasks reference Vietnamese UI requirements.
- Confirm agent rules enforce Vietnamese user-facing copy.


Responsive checks:

- Confirm `MOBILE_RESPONSIVE_REQUIREMENTS.md` exists.
- Confirm FE tasks include responsive foundation.
- Confirm QA tasks include responsive viewport matrix.


Mobile browser checks:

- Confirm `MOBILE_BROWSER_COMPATIBILITY.md` exists.
- Confirm FE tasks include Android/iOS compatibility foundation.
- Confirm QA tasks include Android/iOS browser QA.
